    soot.toDex.instructions  

    • Uses of FiveRegInsn in soot.toDex.instructions

      Classes in soot.toDex.instructions that implement FiveRegInsn 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Insn35c
      The "35c" instruction format: It needs three 16-bit code units, has five registers and is used for method/type items (hence the "c" for "constant pool").

      It is used by the "filled-new-array" opcode and the various "invoke-" opcodes.

      IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: the wide args for "35c" must be explicitly stated - internally, such args are implicitly represented by e.g.
